arCallbacks.szOnCallbackCompleteScript:
function Start(idActorPlayer, sLevelAreaName)
	if sLevelAreaName == S_LEVEL_AREA then
		Hydra.EventSendToActor("PlayerInLevelArea", idSelf, idSelf)
	end
end

function Start()
	if #Hydra.PlayerActorsInLevelArea(S_LEVEL_AREA) > 0 then
		Hydra.EventSendToActor("PlayerInLevelArea", idSelf, idSelf)
	end
end

function Start()
	local sChest = ACTOR_CHEST_REWARD

	if Hydra.QuestGetBonusPhaseResult() then
		sChest = ACTOR_CHEST_REWARD_HEROIC
	end
	
	Events.SpawnRewardChest(CHEST_LOCATION, sChest)
end

arCallbackSets.szOnSetCompleteScript:
Hydra.ActorTriggerSpawnerUpdate(ID_SPAWNER_UNIQUE)
local superElite = Hydra.ActorsInPrefabScopedGroup("EH_Unique")[1]
Hydra.QuestSetCustomParamFromActor(1, superElite)
Hydra.MinimapAddPing(superElite, 10)

Hydra.Wait(0.1)
Hydra.QuestAdvancePhase()

arCallbacks.szOnCallbackCompleteScript:
function Start()
	-- Make sure that any structures destroyed before entering are counted towards the total
	-- For some reason this wasn't working when put in the phase enter so needed to be it's own callback
	Hydra.Wait(0.5)
	nRazeObjectsDestroyed = 3 - Hydra.PrefabScopedActorGroupGetCount("EH_RazeActors")
	if nRazeObjectsDestroyed > 0 then
		Hydra.QuestCallbackCountSet(36 , nRazeObjectsDestroyed)
	end
end

-- This check is needed for the EH Raze event with bells, where the pools spawned by its power belong to the same actorGroup
function Start(idActorSpawned, idActorSpawner)
	if (Hydra.ActorIsValid(idActorSpawner) == false) then
		Hydra.ActorRemoveFromPrefabScopedGroup(idActorSpawned, "EH_RazeActors")
	end
end

function Start(sEventName, idActor, nUserParam)
	for i, enemy in pairs(Hydra.ActorsInPrefabScopedGroup("EH_Unique")) do
		Hydra.ActorKill(enemy)
	end
end

arCallbackSets.szOnSetCompleteScript:
Hydra.Wait(1/60) -- CF: wait a frame to fix bonus race condition
Hydra.QuestAdvancePhase()

arCallbacks.szOnCallbackCompleteScript:
function Start(idActorKiller, idActorKilled)
	if Hydra.ActorGetMonsterRarity(idActorKilled) == Hydra.MR_SUPER_ELITE then
		Hydra.EventSendToActor("SUPER_KILLED", idSelf, idSelf)
		ID_LAST_KILLER = idActorKiller
	end
end

function Start(idActorPlayer, sLevelAreaName)
	if sLevelAreaName == S_LEVEL_AREA and not TableContains(tHasHeardStartConv, idActorPlayer) and Hydra.PlayerIsPrimary(idActorPlayer) then
		TableRemoveInvalidIDs(tHasHeardStartConv) -- so we're not collecting a bunch of garbage ids
		tHasHeardStartConv[#tHasHeardStartConv + 1] = idActorPlayer
	end
end

szUserFunctionsScript:
-- spawn defenders at event target
function SummonDefendersAt(idActor)
	
	if ACTOR_SPAWNER_DEFENDERS then
		
		-- play Minor Wave EG and spawn defenders
		if EG_DEFENDER_SPAWN and Hydra.ActorIsValid(idActor) then
			Hydra.ActorPlayEffectGroup(idActor, EG_DEFENDER_SPAWN)
		end
		
		Hydra.ActorSpawnActor(ACTOR_SPAWNER_DEFENDERS, idActor, false, 0, 0)
	end

end
szOnStartupScript:
tHasHeardStartConv = {}

T_SPAWNERS_MONSTERS = Hydra.ActorsInPrefabScopedGroup("EH_Monster_Spawner")
T_SPAWNERS_ELITE = Hydra.ActorsInPrefabScopedGroup("EH_Elite_Spawner")
T_SPAWNERS_CHAMPIONS = Hydra.ActorsInPrefabScopedGroup("EH_Champion_Spawner")
CHEST_LOCATION = Hydra.ActorsInPrefabScopedGroup("EH_CHEST")[1]
ID_SPAWNER_UNIQUE = Hydra.ActorsInPrefabScopedGroup("EH_Unique_Spawner")[1]

-- spawn normal monsters
local nSpawnerCount = #T_SPAWNERS_MONSTERS
if nSpawnerCount > 0 then
	FYShuffle(T_SPAWNERS_MONSTERS)
	
	for i = 1, nSpawnerCount do
		Hydra.ActorTriggerSpawnerUpdate(T_SPAWNERS_MONSTERS[i])
	end
end

-- spawn extra elite(s)
if #T_SPAWNERS_ELITE > 0 then
	FYShuffle(T_SPAWNERS_ELITE)
	Hydra.ActorTriggerSpawnerUpdate(T_SPAWNERS_ELITE[1])
end

-- spawn champions based on world tier
-- Once this value is > 1 it'll cause champions to spawn (so world tier 3 and up)
-- subtracting 1 instead of 2 because WTs are index 0 in code (so WT3, 2 in code, produces 1 Champ)
local nChampionCount = Hydra.GameGetCurrentWorldTier() - 1
if nChampionCount > 0 and #T_SPAWNERS_CHAMPIONS >= nChampionCount then
	FYShuffle(T_SPAWNERS_CHAMPIONS)
	
	for i = 1, nChampionCount do
		Hydra.ActorTriggerSpawnerUpdate(T_SPAWNERS_CHAMPIONS[i])
	end
end
